<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Indian Events and Festivals</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <style>
        body {
            background-size: cover;
            background-position: center;
            background-attachment: fixed;
            background-image: url("https://i.pinimg.com/564x/09/62/a2/0962a2917f7d69f6eaf1a7dd24b97ed4.jpg");
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        .header {
            background-image: url('header-bg.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 50px 0;
        }

            .header h1 {
                font-size: 48px;
                margin-bottom: 20px;
            }

        .calendar-container {
            padding: 50px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .calendar {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
            justify-items: center;
            align-items: center;
        }

            .calendar .event {
                background-color: #FF9933;
                color: white;
                padding: 20px;
                border-radius: 10px;
                box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
                text-align: center;
                transition: transform 0.3s ease;
            }

                .calendar .event:hover {
                    transform: translateY(-5px);
                }

        .event h3 {
            font-size: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .event p {
            font-size: 16px;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .footer {
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1>Indian Events and Festivals</h1>
        <p>Explore the rich cultural heritage of India through its vibrant festivals and events</p>
    </div>

    <div class="calendar-container">
        <h2>Indian Festival Calendar</h2>
        <div class="calendar"> 
            <div class="event">
                <h3>MakarSakranti</h3>
                <p>This special festival signifies the conclusion of winter and the arrival of a fresh harvest season. In Hinduism, Makar Sankranti is a day devoted to honoring the Sun God.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>Diwali</h3>
                <p>Diwali, also known as the festival of lights, celebrates the victory of light over darkness</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>Holi</h3>
                <p>Holi, the festival of colors, marks the arrival of spring and the end of winter</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>Durga Puja</h3>
                <p>Durga Puja is a celebration of the Hindu goddess Durga and the triumph of good over evil</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>Navratri</h3>
                <p>Navratri is a nine-night festival dedicated to the worship of the Hindu deity Durga</p>
            </div>
        
        </div>
    </div>   
</body>
</html>
